# voicechat per-application routing rules.
#
# Copy to ~/.config/voicechat/rules.conf (or point VOICECHAT_RULES_FILE at it) and edit.
# When this file exists it fully governs per-app behavior; when it doesn't, voicechat uses its
# built-in defaults (desktop shell = clipboard-only, ghostty = ctrl+shift+v, else ctrl+v) plus
# any legacy VOICECHAT_PASTE_RULES. Edits take effect on the next dictation — no restart needed.
#
# Format: one rule per line, whitespace-separated columns, '#' starts a comment.
#   pattern   mode        [option]
#
#   pattern : case-insensitive substring matched against the focused app id ('*' = catch-all).
#             First matching rule wins; '*' is only used if nothing else matched.
#   mode    : paste     -> copy to clipboard AND synthesize a paste keystroke
#             clipboard -> copy to clipboard only, no keystroke
#             emit      -> don't paste; deliver over the broadcast socket only
#                          (still copied to the clipboard as a fallback)
#             system    -> don't paste/copy; broadcast only. Also the AUTOMATIC mode when NO
#                          window is focused (the desktop) — for a system-wide voice command
#                          service (see ~/programming/Plasma/systemvoicecommands).
#   option  : for 'paste', the key combo (e.g. ctrl+v, ctrl+shift+v, shift+insert).
#             Defaults to VOICECHAT_PASTE_KEY, else ctrl+v.
#
# NOTE: matching needs the focus hint — an external listener must populate the active-window
# file (VOICECHAT_ACTIVE_WINDOW_FILE, default ~/.cache/voicechat/active-window) with the focused
# app id. When it reads empty (no window focused — the desktop), the transcript is "system" mode.
#
# EVERY transcript is also broadcast on the Unix socket (VOICECHAT_SOCKET, default
# $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/voicechat.sock) as one JSON line {"text","app","mode","ts"}, regardless of
# mode — so apps can consume it directly. 'emit' just additionally suppresses the local paste.

# Terminals want Ctrl+Shift+V.
ghostty       paste       ctrl+shift+v
kitty         paste       ctrl+shift+v

# Creative apps consume voicechat output via their own integration (forks listening on the
# socket) — don't paste, just emit.
kdenlive      emit
krita         emit
inkscape      emit

# The desktop shell has no real text field — copy only, never synthesize a paste.
plasmashell   clipboard

# Everything else: normal copy + paste.
*             paste       ctrl+v
